\label{lem:NC_from_covering}
    Let $\Gamma$ be a finite, connected, labelled simplicial graph on at least three vertices, and let $\mathcal{L}$ be a collection of induced subgraphs of $\Gamma$ such that:
    \begin{enumerate}
        \item\label{item:nc_sub} For every $\Lambda\in \mathcal{L}$, $A_\Lambda$ does not split over virtually cyclic groups;
        \item\label{item:2edge_seg} Every two-edges segment of $\Gamma$ belongs to some $\Lambda\in \mathcal{L}$.
    \end{enumerate}
    Then $A_\Gamma$ does not split over virtually cyclic groups.
